{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783946947,"nonce":"TGe9uMPEgH6b2P2GLOnfJU1kIIQ=","message":"Fixed and merged as PR #104 (squash `9ea2b31`).\n\nMySQL introspection now reads the `ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` attribute from `information_schema.COLUMNS.EXTRA` into a new structural `ColumnModel.on_update: Option\u003cBox\u003cExprNode\u003e\u003e` (Some(Now)), and the MySQL renderer emits a column-fsp-aware `ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` — so a published table round-trips and the diff converges. PostgreSQL and SQLite reject a column carrying the attribute on every render path, and a new `ColumnCapabilities { on_update }` capability + shape validation makes `check`/preflight reject an unrepresentable or malformed value rather than approving an unpublishable package. KDL gained `on-update-expr` ser/de.\n\nLocal codex review ran to clean over 4 rounds (reject on every path: create-render, PG incremental ALTER, SQLite autoincrement special case, and the capability preflight). Follow-up git-bug 1847e75 (MySQL unique index/constraint prefix lengths) remains open.","files":null}]}